      "versionNonce": 11,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "PASS 2 — UML Relationships  (drawing arrows exposes the gaps)\nGame  has-a -> List<Player>, Board, Dice ; tracks currentPlayerIndex, gameOver\nBoard has -> HashMap<Integer, CellEffect>\nCellEffect (abstract) <|- Snake, Ladder, Bomb        (STRATEGY)\nCellEffect.apply(Player)  --mutates-->  Player.currPos\n\nTHREE QUESTIONS UML FORCES:\n  1) Who rotates turns?  -> GAME owns the list: idx = (idx+1) % size\n  2) Who applies the effect?  -> BOARD.movePlayer (board owns the map)\n  3) Where does overshoot live?  -> BOARD.movePlayer (a movement rule)\nKEY: Player is a PARAMETER to apply(), never a FIELD on the effect\n     (cell 17's snake bites EVERYONE — it belongs to the cell, not a player).",
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "PASS 2 — UML Relationships  (drawing arrows exposes the gaps)\nGame  has-a -> List<Player>, Board, Dice ; tracks currentPlayerIndex, gameOver\nBoard has -> HashMap<Integer, CellEffect>\nCellEffect (abstract) <|- Snake, Ladder, Bomb        (STRATEGY)\nCellEffect.apply(Player)  --mutates-->  Player.currPos\n\nTHREE QUESTIONS UML FORCES:\n  1) Who rotates turns?  -> GAME owns the list: idx = (idx+1) % size\n  2) Who applies the effect?  -> BOARD.movePlayer (board owns the map)\n  3) Where does overshoot live?  -> BOARD.movePlayer (a movement rule)\nKEY: Player is a PARAMETER to apply(), never a FIELD on the effect\n     (cell 17's snake bites EVERYONE — it belongs to the cell, not a player).",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },

